Digital photography has been my go-to for years (it still is in some situations). I often wondered why anyone in their right mind would shoot film... Well, 7 years ago I decided to see for myself what the hype was about and here we are...

Here are three reasons (of many) I prefer to Shoot Film:

1. Authenticity: Film captures a raw and timeless quality that digital cannot replicate. The grain, colors, and imperfections add a unique charm to each image, enhancing the emotional depth of the portraits.

2. Intimacy: Shooting film creates a more intimate and personal experience for both the photographer and the client. The slower pace of shooting film encourages a deeper connection, allowing the client to feel more comfortable and vulnerable in front of the camera.

3. Artistic Expression: Film offers a greater range of artistic possibilities, allowing me to experiment with different film stocks, exposures, and techniques. This artistic freedom enables me to create truly one-of-a-kind portraits that reflect the individuality and uniqueness of each client. 

Despite the rising cost of shooting film, these benefits far outweigh the expense. The tangible and emotional value that film brings to the table is unparalleled, creating a truly unforgettable experience and delivering exceptional results for me and my clients.

#FilmPhotography #AuthenticPortraits #IntimateMoments #FilmPhotographer #ArtisticPortraits #FilmArtistry

Self love and body positivity are essential for our overall well-being. Embracing and accepting ourselves, including our bodies, is crucial for a healthy mindset. By practicing self love, we acknowledge our worth and value as individuals. It allows us to take good care of our bodies and appreciate all they do for us, instead of hyper focusing on our perceived flaws. Body positivity encourages us to celebrate diversity and recognize that beauty comes in all shapes and sizes.
Remember, you are unique and deserving of love and acceptance just as you are.
